┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 🔴 CRITICAL-1 │ Tailwind CSS CDN in Production                              │
│ File: index.html, Line 8                                                    │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Problem:
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>

  Why it happens:
    The developer used the Tailwind CDN for convenience during development and
    never replaced it with a proper build-time integration. Tailwind themselves
    print a warning about this on every page load.

  What happens at runtime:
    1. Browser downloads the entire 1.2MB Tailwind JS engine
    2. Engine scans the full DOM to discover all CSS class names in use
    3. Generates CSS on-the-fly for each discovered class
    4. Only THEN can the page render with correct styling
    5. This entire process blocks rendering on every single visit

  Impact: +800ms to +1,500ms on every cold page load

  Fix — Step A: Install Tailwind as a build-time dependency
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    npm install -D tailwindcss autoprefixer postcss

  Fix — Step B: Create tailwind.config.js
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    /** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
    export default {
      content: [
        "./index.html",
        "./**/*.{ts,tsx}",
      ],
      theme: { extend: {} },
      plugins: [],
    }

  Fix — Step C: Update vite.config.ts
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // BEFORE (current):
    export default defineConfig({
      plugins: [react()],
    });

    // AFTER (fixed):
    import tailwindcss from '@tailwindcss/vite';
    export default defineConfig({
      plugins: [react(), tailwindcss()],
      build: {
        rollupOptions: {
          output: {
            manualChunks: {
              vendor:  ['react', 'react-dom'],
              charts:  ['recharts'],
              icons:   ['lucide-react'],
              ai:      ['@google/genai'],
              db:      ['@supabase/supabase-js', 'dexie'],
            }
          }
        }
      }
    });

  Fix — Step D: Remove CDN tag from index.html
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // DELETE this line from index.html:
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>

    // ADD Tailwind directives to a new src/index.css:
    @tailwind base;
    @tailwind components;
    @tailwind utilities;

  Result: CSS drops from 1.2MB (runtime engine) to ~10–15KB (purged, minified)


