  Why it happens:
    vite build has never been run. The app runs as raw TSX source files
    processed at runtime. esm.sh acts as a live npm registry — every cold
    visit must fetch each package over the network.

  Cold load impact per package:
    esm.sh/react              → ~120 KB
    esm.sh/react-dom          → ~180 KB
    esm.sh/dexie              → ~85  KB
    esm.sh/recharts           → ~320 KB  (pulls d3-* dependencies)
    esm.sh/lucide-react       → ~450 KB  (all 562 icons, user needs ~30)
    esm.sh/@google/genai      → ~200 KB
    ─────────────────────────────────────
    TOTAL cold                → ~1,355 KB extra (1.3 MB)

  Impact: +1,000ms to +3,000ms on cold loads

  Fix:
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    # THE SINGLE MOST IMPORTANT COMMAND:
    npm run build

    # Then deploy the /dist folder to Vercel (not the source root)
    # Vercel CLI:
    vercel --prod
    # OR: drag /dist into Vercel dashboard

  What this does:
    - React bundled + minified + gzip'd → ~40KB
    - lucide-react tree-shaken → only 30 icons used → ~15KB (not 450KB)
    - recharts + d3 bundled → ~180KB (not 320KB per CDN)
    - All imports resolved locally — zero esm.sh requests
    - Total JS: ~300–350KB (was 2.5–4.5MB)


