└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Problem:
    // Runs every 10 seconds — forever
    this.syncInterval = setInterval(() => this.syncAll(), 10000);

    // syncAll() calls these sequentially:
    await this.syncTable('workouts',        'workouts');
    await this.syncTable('meals',           'meals');
    await this.syncTable('progress',        'progress');
    await this.syncTable('photos',          'photos');
    await this.syncTable('splits',          'splits');
    await this.syncTable('activeProtocol',  'active_protocol');
    await this.syncTable('activeDiet',      'active_diet');
    await this.syncTable('profile',         'profiles');

  Why it's harmful:
    - 8 Supabase calls every 10 seconds, even when nothing changed
    - Competes with user-triggered queries for connection budget
    - On Supabase Free Tier with shared compute, this degrades response
      times for ALL other queries
    - On mobile: drains battery and data

  Fix:
    // BEFORE (sync.ts):
    startBackgroundSync() {
      this.syncInterval = setInterval(() => this.syncAll(), 10000); // ← REMOVE
      window.addEventListener('online', () => this.syncAll());
    }

    // AFTER — event-driven only:
    startBackgroundSync() {
      // Sync when network comes back online
      window.addEventListener('online', () => this.syncAll());

      // Sync when user returns to the tab (app comes to foreground)
      document.addEventListener('visibilitychange', () => {
        if (!document.hidden) this.syncAll();
      });

      // One-time initial sync on app start (with delay to not compete with load)
      setTimeout(() => this.syncAll(), 3000);
      // No setInterval — sync is now purely event-driven
    }

  Impact: Eliminates 8 background Supabase calls every 10 seconds.


