┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ 🟠 MAJOR-8 │ No vercel.json — Zero Asset Caching                           │
│ File: Missing from project root                                             │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  Problem:
    No caching headers are configured. Every revisit re-validates all assets
    with the server. Hashed JS and CSS files should be cached for 1 year
    (immutable) since the hash guarantees uniqueness per build.

  Fix — Create vercel.json in project root:
    {
      "headers": [
        {
          "source": "/assets/(.*)",
          "headers": [
            {
              "key": "Cache-Control",
              "value": "public, max-age=31536000, immutable"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "source": "/(.*)",
          "headers": [
            {
              "key": "Cache-Control",
              "value": "public, max-age=0, must-revalidate"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "rewrites": [
        { "source": "/(.*)", "destination": "/index.html" }
      ]
    }

  The rewrites section also fixes SPA routing — prevents 404 on direct URL access.


